results.name: a(n) is the smallest initial value (a prime) for the Euclid-Mullin (EM) sequence in which the p=5 prime emerges as n-th term, i.e., arises at the n-th position.
comment: The sequence is not monotonic and it seems that p=5 may arise at any position > 2. a(2)=0 means that 5 is never the 2nd term in an EM sequence of A000945-type because a(2)=2 or 3.
example: The sequence for 17 is 17, 2, 5, ... where the 5 is at the third place, therefore a(3)=17.
results.author: _Labos Elemer_, May 04 2004
ext: a(16) = 449 was conjectured by _R. J. Mathar_ and confirmed by _Don Reble_, Oct 07 2006
